<TITLE> Bangladesh artworks on display in NY </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 21 (bdnews24.com) - An exhibition of artworks of 34 Bangladeshi artists began at the Turkish Cultural and Tourism Centre near UN Plaza in New York Thursday, the government said in a statement. The Bangladesh mission to the United Nations and Bengal Gallery of Fine Arts in Dhaka co-organised the nine-day event that would end on March 28. A total of 42 artworks have been put on show, the statement said Friday. Permanent representative of Bangladesh to the UN Ismat Jahan inaugurated the exhibition, where Ralph Samuelson, director of the Asian Cultural Council in New York, Subir Chowdhury, Bengal Gallery of Fine Arts director, and artist Rafiqunnabi were present. At the inaugural session, Ismat Jahan said such shows would help Bangladesh's rich arts and culture reach the international community. bdnew
